---
import StorefrontShell from '../layouts/StorefrontShell.astro';
---

<StorefrontShell
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How BuddyBubble collects, uses, and protects your information, including SMS-related data."
>
  <section>
    <p>
      BuddyBubble (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;) operates the BuddyBubble service (the
      &ldquo;Service&rdquo;). This Privacy Policy describes how we handle personal information when you use our
      websites, applications, and related features. By using the Service, you agree to this policy and our Terms of
      Service.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following categories of information, depending on how you use BuddyBubble:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Account and profile data</strong> — such as name, email address, authentication identifiers, and
        preferences you provide when you create or manage an account.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Workspace and community data</strong> — information you or your organization add to BuddyBubbles
        (workspaces), including messages, tasks, files, and member lists, as permitted by your role and settings.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Usage and technical data</strong> — such as device or browser type, general location derived from IP
        address, log data, and usage events that help us operate, secure, and improve the Service.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Communications</strong> — information you send to us (for example, support requests) and records of
        transactional or service-related messages we send to you, where applicable.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How we use information</h2>
    <p>We use personal information to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide, maintain, and improve the Service and its features;</li>
      <li>Authenticate users, prevent fraud and abuse, and protect the security of the Service;</li>
      <li>Send administrative notices, security alerts, and (where permitted) product updates;</li>
      <li>Comply with law, enforce our terms, and respond to lawful requests; and</li>
      <li>Analyze usage in aggregate or de-identified form to understand how the Service is used.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We do not use mobile information for third-party marketing as described in the SMS section below.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sharing</h2>
    <p>
      We may share information with service providers that process data on our behalf (for example, hosting, email
      delivery, analytics, and security). They are contractually required to use information only to provide services
      to us. We may also share information if required by law, to protect rights and safety, or as part of a business
      transfer (for example, a merger) subject to appropriate safeguards. Where you participate in a workspace, other
      members may see content you submit according to that workspace&rsquo;s settings and your role.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>SMS and mobile information</h2>
    <p>
      If you or your organization choose to receive text messages from BuddyBubble (for example, alerts or
      operational notices sent via an SMS program), we collect and use mobile-related data only as needed to deliver
      those messages, comply with carrier and regulatory requirements, and support the Service.
    </p>
    <p class="rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-100/80 p-4 text-amber-950">
      No mobile information will be shared with third parties/affiliates for marketing/promotional purposes. All other
      categories exclude text messaging originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with
      any third parties.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      We implement administrative, technical, and organizational measures designed to protect personal information
      against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. No method of transmission over the Internet is completely secure; we
      work to maintain safeguards appropriate to the nature of the data we process.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide the Service, comply with
      legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. Retention periods may vary by data category and
      context.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Your rights and choices</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may have the right to access, correct, delete, or port certain personal
      information, or to object to or restrict some processing. You can manage some information through your account
      settings. You may also opt out of non-essential marketing communications. To exercise rights or ask questions, contact
      us using the information below. We will respond in line with applicable law.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Children</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is not directed to children under 13 (or the age required by your jurisdiction), and we do not knowingly
      collect personal information from children in that category without appropriate consent. If you believe we have
      collected such information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>International users</h2>
    <p>
      We may process and store information in the United States and other countries where we or our providers operate.
      By using the Service, you understand that your information may be transferred to countries that may have different
      data protection rules than your country, subject to appropriate safeguards as required by law.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post the updated version on this page and, where
      appropriate, provide additional notice. Your continued use of the Service after changes become effective
      constitutes acceptance of the updated policy, except where your consent is required.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For privacy-related requests or questions, use the support or help options in the BuddyBubble application, or
      contact us through the channels published on our website.
    </p>
  </section>
</StorefrontShell>
